description.narrative: In 2019, UNICEF continued to support the production of data and evidence for planning and budgeting. Highlights included the publication of the SDG Child Databook, a user-friendly compilation of official child-related statistics, technical support for the preparation of the 2020 Census questionnaire, and the development of a new situation analysis of children (SitAn). Large-scale consultations were held with adolescents to inform this situation analysis, and beyond it the development of the new UNICEF country programme. UNICEF continued to promote a monitoring and evaluation culture, with training and video tutorials on real-time monitoring, and with substantial support to the UNDAF evaluation. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:07/02/2020
